Story Time-

I was going through one of the lowest phases of my life- dealing with a lot of personal struggles. From injuries to inconsistent practice, from not feeling satisfied with my progress to simply not being sure about where I was headed whether in life or with dance - it was a rough time (hopefully it ends very soon)

Then came this one event. I showed up, not expecting much. I wasn’t even sure why I was there maybe just to feel some energy, hoping it would help me open up, even just a little.

And then, I was against someone I’ve trained and grown with, someone who knows me inside out. We were set to battle. But this wasn’t just any battle. It became one of the most opened up me.

Because in that battle, I let go. I poured everything out every emotion I had been holding in. No one ever really knows what someone else is going through, but in that moment, I expressed it all through movement.

I’m incredibly grateful to have people around me who push me, who are honest with me, who help me grow- not just as a dancer, but as a person.

This battle was just the beginning. I’m hopeful for what’s ahead, and I’m ready to move forward from here.

Thank you god & that special person for always being there🤍
